10 An Act relating to deed regulation; amending 59 O.S.
2021, Sections 858-307.2 and 858-351, which relate to
11 real estate licensing; requiring certain continuing
education course; expanding application of certain
12 definitions; defining term; updating statutory
language; requiring certain notification to buyer;
13 requiring the Oklahoma Real Estate Commission to
promulgate certain rules; providing for codification;
14 and providing an effective date.
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 858-307.2,
18 is amended to read as follows:
19 Section 858-307.2. A. Beginning November 1, 2004, as a
20 condition of renewal or reactivation of the a real estate license,
21 each licensee with the exception of those exempt as set out in this
22 section shall submit to the Oklahoma Real Estate Commission evidence
23 of completion of a specified number of hours of continuing education
24 courses approved by the Commission, within the thirty-six (36)
